# sources.conf — repos that collect-raw.sh scans for context.
# Copy to sources.conf and edit:   cp tools/sources.conf.example tools/sources.conf
#
# One path per line. Lines starting with # are ignored.
# Paths can be absolute (/Users/you/code/app), ~-relative (~/code/app),
# or $HOME-relative (Documents/projects/app).
#
# For each repo, collect-raw.sh pulls (redacted): CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, README.md,
# docs/**/*.md, other root *.md, and the full git log.

Documents/projects/my-app
Documents/projects/my-other-repo
# ~/work/some-service
